30/11/2003
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- KFOR announced on Friday (28 November) that its troops have tightened security in Pristina in response to a "specific" terrorist threat. KFOR spokesman Chris Thompson told reporters that international organisations could be the targets, but he would not name the offices at risk. UN police spokeswoman Angela Joseph said that the force was aware of a "general threat against foreign government offices and police buildings in Pristina". (AP, AFP, B92, Reuters - 28/11/03)
